DC  Galactose metabolism
DR  KEGG; map00052;
DC  Lactose and galactose degradation I
DR  MetaCyc; LACTOSECAT-PWY;
CC  Galactose-6-phosphate is degraded via the tagatose-6-phosphate pathway, 
CC  which is a 3 step pathway encoded by the lacABCD gene cluster of the 
CC  lactose-PTS (lactose phosphotransferase) operon. The three enzymes in 
CC  the pathway are galactose-6-phosphate isomerase (this requires both 
CC  LacA and LacB subunits for activity), tagatose-6-phosphate kinase 
CC  (LacC), and tagatose 1,6-diphosphate aldolase (LacD)[1]. 
